Documentation

Bluestone Editor writes Markdown in a WYSIWYG way. After writing the document, it will be automatically converted to markdown format and saved locally. It uses the syntax of GitHub Flavored Markdownand extends the rendering of mermiad graphics and katex formulas . 中文文档

Bluestone editor is open source, related links github

Assuming you already have a basic understanding of Mardkown

Format

Text format can be converted with floating bar or syntax

The text format is triggered by the last character. If it is bold, enter the last * to convert it. When you want to leave the text format, you can use the left and right arrow keys. For the format type, you can check the system menu Format

Markdown Elements

For relevant operation shortcut keys, please refer to the system menu

Title

Enter and exit 1-5 # signs at the beginning of the paragraph, adding spaces can be converted into 1-5 level headings

Bockquote

Enter >at the beginning of the paragraph to add space conversion, the result is as follows

blockquote

pictures and links

use ![alt][link] format to write pictures，at last]characters are used to trigger conversions，The same is true for linking behavior，Links support http backlinks and file links such as：./markdown.md 

Screenshots can be copied directly into the editing area, and if the folder is not opened, the picture will be automatically saved to the system scratch area, and in the case of opening the folder, the picture will be saved in the root directory '.images' folder

Usually, when importing a link or picture by filePath, you can drag it from the file tree, or use syntax conversion and shortcut keys to insert.

List

Use 1 or  or - with a space to convert to an ordered or unordered list, enter  with a space to convert to an ordered or unordered list, enter [ ] and a space at the beginning of a list item to convert the list to a task list, or you can use shortcut keys to manipulate it.

Type cmd+enter into a list item to insert multiple paragraphs into the list item For example:

  1. list item1

  2. list item2

    Nested paragraph 1

    Nested paragraph 2

  3. list item3

Github Table

Enter the format |title1|title2| at the beginning of the paragraph to automatically create a table with 2 columns。

and use cmd+enter to create the next line, Use  to create the next line, Use cmd+shift+backspace to delete the current row, and more operations can be viewed by right-clicking on each cell.

Code Fences

Start typing in the paragraph

md
```language

Add carriage return to convert to code snippet input area, click in the upper right corner to switch languages, and type cmd+enter in the code block to jump out of the code block.

The rendering is as follows:

go
package main

import "fmt"

func main() {
  for true  {
    fmt.Printf("loop happy\n");
  }
}

Bluestone highlights the code according to shiki, and the highlighting language is very rich, which can be viewed for details languages

Footnote

The syntax is as follows

md
Please check for details [^keyword]

[^keyword]: Here are the keyword annotations

The editor will automatically highlight the text and click cmd+click to position

Mermaid and Katex

When a code snippet uses the Mermaid language, the Mermaid graphic will be automatically rendered below it, the cursor will leave the snippet area, and the snippet will automatically collapse.

Type $$ at the beginning of the paragraph to add a carriage enter, the Katex formula editing area will be created, the Katex formula will be automatically rendered below it, the cursor leaves the snippet area, and the snippet is automatically collapsed. An example figure is as follows:

Auto save

The document will be automatically saved after 3 seconds of change, and it will be automatically saved when the application is closed, in between, you can also type cmd+s to save manually.

After the document is changed, the * sign appears after the file name on the navigation bar, the  sign appears after the file name on the navigation bar, the * sign disappears and it is saved.

Export

Support exporting pdf, html, and ebook.

This html document is exported by the editor.

An eBook is a document that combines multiple documents into one document by chapter and is equipped with a search function.

Select Export eBook, and Choose a custom chapter.

Will merge multiple documents in to a html, convert pictures to base64, and internal links will jump to each other.

Common problem

html rendering

Bluestone uses a pure rich text editing mode, Direct writing and rendering HTML code is not supported for the time being, and can use code snippets to render, Click the eye icon to render the html directly，such as:

Export as:

md
```html render
<p style="text-align:center;color:cyan;">hello bluestone</p>

code snippet performance

Bluestone uses the shiki high precision shader instead of the code editor to render code fragments. After the number of codes is higher than 500-1000 lines, there may be an input delay problem. It is recommended not to add more than 1000 lines of code to a code segment, which can be divided into multiple segments.

In the future, we will try to add an optional code rendering method, switching from the shader to the code editor.
